## Economics-Specific Acronyms

### Standard acronyms (don't spell out every time):
- EITC (Earned Income Tax Credit) - spell out first use
- GDP (Gross Domestic Product) - spell out first use
- CPI (Consumer Price Index) - spell out first use
- ACS (American Community Survey) - spell out first use
- PSID (Panel Study of Income Dynamics) - spell out first use

**Convention:** Spell out on first use with acronym in parentheses, then use acronym.

### Don't create acronyms for:
- Terms used only 2-3 times (just spell out)
- Short phrases (3-4 words)
- Terms readers need to understand fully each time

**Key principle:** Acronyms should aid reading, not create cognitive load.
